# assets/legacy-css/ holds vendor CSS downloaded verbatim from Turbify's CDN (see
# docs/2026-07-prelaunch-audit.md and the Turbify-CSS-localization milestone). Mark it
# binary so git never applies line-ending conversion -- the whole point is preserving the
# exact bytes as served, and this machine's core.autocrlf=true would otherwise silently
# rewrite LF to CRLF on checkout/commit (same class of issue documented in build/README.md
# for generated pages).
assets/legacy-css/*.css -text
